OL,3,C'Revolutionary' skin sensor could
OL,4,Cchange how eczema is treated
OL,6,FDr Sara Medina-Lombardero, a research
OL,7,Fassociate at Heriot-Watt University
OL,8,Fwho is leading the patient and user
OL,9,Fclinical development of the
OL,10,Ftechnology, added: "The planned
OL,11,Fclinical evaluation will allow us to
OL,12,Fconfidently correlate our objective
OL,13,Fmeasurements to those of specialist
OL,14,Fdermatologist assessments.
OL,16,F"Success will set us on a path where
OL,17,Fthe sensor could enable treatment
OL,18,Ftracking and diagnoses to be made in
OL,19,Flocal pharmacies and community
OL,20,Fhealthcare facilities."
